 students to spend extra time on assignments to make them “cool.”',1,1,1405098638,1407177025,1,1,0,0,0),(64,64,'tip','und','Teach students how to reduce larger problems into smaller algorithms they can easily implement.',1,1,1405098702,1407183650,1,1,0,0,0),(65,65,'tip','und','Simulate the execution of recursion by diagrammatic tracing to help improve understanding.',1,1,1405098791,1407183611,1,1,0,0,0),(66,66,'tip','und','Pool all available resources to maximize the benefit that can be drawn from them.',1,1,1405458111,1407183552,1,1,0,0,0),(67,67,'tip','und','Have assignments grow in difficulty periodically rather than progressively so that students get breaks.',1,1,1405458650,1405458650,1,1,0,0,0),(68,68,'tip','und','Motivate your students by setting goals and connecting with them individually.',1,1,1405459473,1405459473,1,1,0,0,0),(69,69,'tip','und','Share your own experiences and struggles because students may find insight in how you overcame and understood different topics.',1,1,1405459582,1405459582,1,1,0,0,0),(70,70,'tip','und','Remind students \"It\'s not that you don\'t know it. It\'s that you don\'t know it yet.\"',1,1,1405459682,1405459682,1,1,0,0,0),(71,71,'tip','und','Tell students “It’s not about understanding immediately, but not giving up and trying until you do.”',1,1,1405460113,1405460113,1,1,0,0,0),(72,72,'tip','und','Asking students how they are doing on assignments keeps them accountable and identifies unproductive students when necessary.',1,1,1405460182,1405460182,1,1,0,0,0),(73,73,'tip','und','If students are worried about starting an assignment, give them an explicit first step.',1,1,1405460243,1405460243,1,1,0,0,0),(74,74,'tip','und','Provide notes or videos that highlight important concepts of the homework to help navigate students through more difficult or involved parts of an assignment.',1,1,1405460295,1405460295,1,1,0,0,0),(75,75,'tip','und','After returning a test or exam, speak with your class about how they feel and what they can do