553359,1405553359,1,1,0,0,0),(115,115,'tip','und','Motivate students by showing them examples of what they will be learning to create.',1,1,1405553430,1405553430,1,1,0,0,0),(116,116,'tip','und','Look for a textbook with good examples, not just good explanations.',1,1,1405553525,1405553525,1,1,0,0,0),(117,117,'tip','und','When doing web development, have students run their code in multiple browsers to ensure compatibility.',1,1,1405553613,1405553613,1,1,0,0,0),(118,118,'tip','und','Watch Computer Science-related TED talks with your class to stimulate interest in the course.',1,1,1405553882,1405553882,1,1,0,0,0),(119,119,'tip','und','Limit the number of choices available to students in an assignment to ensure that students have enough time to complete an assignment.',1,1,1405553955,1405553955,1,1,0,0,0),(120,120,'tip','und','Assign smaller, similar projects before a relatively big project so students are more equipped to start and complete it.',1,1,1405554005,1405554005,1,1,0,0,0),(121,121,'tip','und','Be aware of students’ math background so you can prepare material to scaffold students for course content.',1,1,1405554059,1405554059,1,1,0,0,0),(122,122,'tip','und','Prepare example projects and code to inspire students and clarify expectations.',1,1,1405554269,1405554333,1,1,0,0,0),(123,123,'tip','und','Have students clearly outline who their audience is when designing a project so they can tailor to the users’ needs.',1,1,1405554656,1407178253,1,1,0,0,0),(124,124,'tip','und','To ensure equitable access in your classroom, don’t allow language reinforcing the idea that computer science is “guy stuff” in the classroom, even passively.',1,1,1405554781,1407182620,1,1,0,0,0),(125,125,'tip','und','Speak to students directly if they use language that downplays the ability of women and students of color.',1,1,1405554901,1407182835,1,1,0,0,0),(126,126,'tip','und','Take the time to encourage girls and students of color as they often internalize cultural expectations that they have little innate CS ability.',1,1,1405554983,1407178492,1,1,0,0,0),(127,127,'tip','und','Allocate computer time evenly among students, especially in elementary school, so all students get a chance to play.',1,1,1405555124,1407194921,1,1,0,0,0),(128,128,'tip','und','Write made-up examples to avoid unknowingly introducing culturally-biased problems.',1,1,1405555366,1407173858,1,1,0,0,0),(129,129,'tip','und','Ensure that students and counselors understand how CS is more than simply “a vocational skill” by highlighting how CS helps make critical thinkers and problem-solvers, too.',1,1,1405555499,1407182592,1,1,0,0,0),(130,130,'tip','und','To engage a wider range of students in intro courses, be sure to highlight on the real-world context and applications of CS.',1,1,1405555616,1407182773,1,1,0,0,0),(131,131,'tip','und','Show students the diverse set of people who hold CS careers. Make sure it’s clear that there is no one person, or one personality that exemplifies the field.',1,1,1405555698,1407203377,1,1,0,0,0),(132,132,'tip','und','Ask students what they like about programming—it lets you know what to focus on so that students remain interested.',1,1,1405555812,1407177055,1,1,0,0,0),(133,133,'tip','und','Don’t conflate interest in computer science with excessive amounts of time spent coding. This can discourage students who feel like they’re not into computer science because they don’t obsess over it.',1,1,1405555934,1407173645,1,1,0,0,0),(134,134,'tip','und','Having high expectations, while important, is not sufficient for students’ success in CS.',1,1,1405556148,1405556148,1,1,0,0,0),(135,135,'tip','und','Have students walk through and explain code to check for understanding.',1,1,1405556232,1405556232,1,1,0,0,0),(136,136,'tip','und','Find examples that help motivate difficult abstract concepts, like passing in a value to a function.',1,1,1405556315,1405556315,1,1,0,0,0),(137,137,'tip','und','To help students understand how a while loop executes, teach them that it runs “until” a condition is satisfied.',1,1,1405556393,1405556393,1,1,0,0,0),(138,138,'tip','und','Provide open-ended prompts for building projects to keep students motivated. ',1,1,1405556465,1405556465,1,1,0,0,0),(139,139,'tip','und','Remind girls that women in CS can have positive social impact to interest them in tech careers.',1,1,1405556653,1407182556,1,1,0,0,0),(140,140,'tip','und','Have parents and peers also encourage students’ interest in Computer Science and problem solving to help influence their pursuit of it.',1,1,1405556725,1407182516,1,1,0,0,0),(141,141,'tip','und','Use puzzles, etc. in assignments and activities to build students’ confidence and interest in pursuing Computer Science.',1,1,1405556809,1407182366,1,1,0,0,0),(142,142,'tip','und','Students tend to make assumptions about computer science based on the experiences they’ve already had with computers.',1,1,1405557116,1407182323,1,1,0,0,0),(143,143,'tip','und','When designing CS courses for total novices, write some assignments that allow students to make familiar or interesting things, e.g. making games or animations.',1,1,1405557223,1407178081,1,1,0,0,0),(144,144,'tip','und','Ensure young CS students check their functions with a variety of inputs, as well as with edge cases.',1,1,1405557298,1407200091,1,1,0,0,0),(145,145,'tip','und','Beginning students are used to viewing computers from a user’s perspective, and they subsequently have habits that may conflict with using the computer as a programmer.',1,1,1405557455,1407177232,1,1,0,0,0),(146,146,'tip','und','Encourage new CS students to break away from the habit of using an interface to solve computer problems.',1,1,1405557575,1407177452,1,1,0,0,0),(147,147,'tip','und','When designing early CS courses, use tools with familiar interfaces, like programs with drag and drop components.',1,1,1405557679,1407192252,1,1,0,0,0),(148,148,'tip','und','Gradually increase the grading strictness about styling to help students become more meticulous about naming and documentation. ',1,1,1405557750,1407190147,1,1,0,0,0),(149,149,'tip','und','Emphasize the importance of planning and analyzing code to students with previous CS experience.',1,1,1405557924,1407178514,1,1,0,0,0),(150,150,'tip','und','When students consider a function that produces incorrect outputs to be working, assign problems that provide clear on-screen feedback when a function is incorrect.',1,1,1405558080,1407200692,1,1,0,0,0),(151,151,'tip','und','Build your course around \"big ideas\" that are motivated by \"essential questions\" to excite students.',1,1,1405627245,1407201055,1,1,0,0,0),(152,152,'tip','und','Demonstrate the technology students will be learning about in class to motivate them.',1,1,1405627353,1407177797,1,1,0,0,0),(153,153,'tip','und','Provide students with high level explanations of how the technology they’re using works.',1,1,1405627430,1407185493,1,1,0,0,0),(154,154,'tip','und','Give students ways to visualize their algorithms in action.',1,1,1405627503,1407178056,1,1,0,0,0),(155,155,'tip','und','Have students experiment with technology they use in class to “test its accuracy and uncover its limitations.”',1,1,1405627597,1407202677,1,1,0,0,0),(156,156,'tip','und','Have students summarize what they’ve learned in addition to answering quiz questions and solving small problems.',1,1,1405627713,1407178153,1,1,0,0,0),(157,157,'tip','und','To avoid the misconception that variables store unresolved equations, remind students that variables always resolve expressions to a value or an object.',1,1,1405703415,1407173352,1,1,0,0,0),(158,158,'tip','und','Remind students that variable assignment occurs in the order assignments are given. This avoids the misconception that changing one value affects other variables assigned before it.',1,1,1405703501,1407178035,1,1,0,0,0),(159,159,'tip','und','Avoid using x and y as variable names to prevent students from confusing variable assignments with mathematical expressions.',1,1,1405703590,1407178131,1,1,0,0,0),(160,160,'tip','und','To avoid confusion about the \"lifetime\" of values and objects, remind students that values and objects must be explicitly assigned to variables if they are to be used later.',1,1,1405703685,1407173275,1,1,0,0,0),(161,161,'tip','und','Introduce the concept of the \'state of an object\' early on when teaching object oriented programming.',1,1,1405703789,1407178324,1,1,0,0,0),(162,162,'tip','und','Be explicit about what direction references point when teaching about objects and references.',1,1,1405703866,1407178554,1,1,0,0,0),(163,163,'tip','und','Use the \"PB&J\" sandwich activity to introduce important components of algorithms.',1,1,1405717559,1407193285,1,1,0,0,0),(164,164,'tip','und','Use questions where students have to pick out lines of code that are useless or unnecessary in producing the desired result of a function in order to assess understanding. ',1,1,1405717859,1405964620,1,1,0,0,0),(165,165,'tip','und','Use questions that ask students to predict the result of a function in order to assess understanding.',1,1,1405717966,1405962852,1,1,0,0,0),(166,166,'tip','und','Ask questions periodically to your class while watching instructional videos to keep students focused and engaged.',1,1,1405718176,1405962582,1,1,0,0,0),(167,167,'tip','und','Emphasize to your students that in languages like Java a semicolon ends a ‘complete thought,’ rather than just a line of code.',1,1,1405958449,1407190787,1,1,0,0,0),(168,168,'tip','und','Prioritize straightforward, understandable code over unclear, shortcut-filled code to avoid confusion.',1,1,1405958632,1407178431,1,1,0,0,0),(169,169,'tip','und','Avoid taking shortcuts! Students will model your behavior and ultimately miss important fundamental concepts.',1,1,1405958700,1407201896,1,1,0,0,0),(170,170,'tip','und','Ensure loops and conditionals are consistently formatted.',1,1,1405958788,1407178183,1,1,0,0,0),(171,171,'faq','und','FAQ',1,1,1406851303,1406851303,2,1,0,0,0),(172,172,'sigcse15','und','sigcse15',1,1,1412289953,1412289953,0,1,0,0,0);
