ctations about prerequisite knowledge so all students are well-equipped for class material.','',1405035822,1,1,1,0),(48,48,1,'Improving ineffective assignments by modifying or altogether replacing them increases learning overall.','',1405982631,1,1,1,0),(49,49,1,'Make sure students have the necessary information on how to set up their computing environment to work comfortably and effectively.','',1405036060,1,1,1,0),(50,50,1,'Go beyond prescribed course content to teach students about additional tools and skills they need to be successful.','',1405979236,1,1,1,0),(51,51,1,'Model how breaking down a problem into bite-size pieces can be an important tool for success.','',1405979261,1,1,1,0),(52,52,1,'Teach students how to trace out-of-bounds errors by demonstrating on the board.','',1405036543,1,1,1,0),(53,53,1,'Use a diagram with variable-value pairs for each call of a recursive function to help students see the change of control flow as calls are made and completed.','',1405036730,1,1,1,0),(54,54,1,'Explain through metaphor that return values allow a primary function to get information from a secondary function.','',1405036783,1,1,1,0),(55,55,1,'Emphasize that it is not necessary to add an \'&\' in C++ when passing an argument to a function that takes in a reference. ','',1405036975,1,1,1,0),(56,56,1,'Avoid using technical jargon when introducing new material to help students understand course content.','',1405037069,1,1,1,0),(57,57,1,'Encourage students to write the inside of the loop before the loop syntax to help students recognize the conditions necessary for iteration.','',1405037112,1,1,1,0),(58,58,1,'Direct students struggling with loops to write on paper what should happen and then have them determine the start, end, and update values.','',1405037153,1,1,1,0),(59,59,1,'Encourage students to step away from buggy code and think about the big picture as a part of the debugging process.','',1405037200,1,1,1,0),(60,60,1,'Encourage students to develop solutions in