nd y as variable names to prevent students from confusing variable assignments with mathematical expressions.','',1407178131,1,1,1,0),(160,160,1,'To avoid confusion about the \"lifetime\" of values and objects, remind students that values and objects must be explicitly assigned to variables if they are to be used later.','',1407173275,1,1,1,0),(161,161,1,'Introduce the concept of the \'state of an object\' early on when teaching object oriented programming.','',1407178324,1,1,1,0),(162,162,1,'Be explicit about what direction references point when teaching about objects and references.','',1407178554,1,1,1,0),(163,163,1,'Use the \"PB&J\" sandwich activity to introduce important components of algorithms.','',1407193285,1,1,1,0),(164,164,1,'Use questions where students have to pick out lines of code that are useless or unnecessary in producing the desired result of a function in order to assess understanding. ','',1405964620,1,1,1,0),(165,165,1,'Use questions that ask students to predict the result of a function in order to assess understanding.','',1405962852,1,1,1,0),(166,166,1,'Ask questions periodically to your class while watching instructional videos to keep students focused and engaged.','',1405962582,1,1,1,0),(167,167,1,'Emphasize to your students that in languages like Java a semicolon ends a ‘complete thought,’ rather than just a line of code.','',1407190787,1,1,1,0),(168,168,1,'Prioritize straightforward, understandable code over unclear, shortcut-filled code to avoid confusion.','',1407178431,1,1,1,0),(169,169,1,'Avoid taking shortcuts! Students will model your behavior and ultimately miss important fundamental concepts.','',1407201896,1,1,1,0),(170,170,1,'Ensure loops and conditionals are consistently formatted.','',1407178183,1,1,1,0),(171,171,1,'FAQ','',1406851303,1,2,1,0),(172,172,1,'sigcse15','',1412289953,1,0,1,0);
